    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carved heads or faces, usually having fierce expressions, exagerated features, and bulbous eyes. Examples are faces of ancestors located on Maori meeting houses. For faces carved with a more realistic appearance, used for gables of houses or canoes, use parata.</Note_Text>
